      "writtenOn": "2020-03-16T20:43:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Be specific and name the architecture that you’re defining things for.\n\nAlso, everywhere you have this kind of thing, you should standardize on the order that you present architectures. In the companion .h, you chose the opposite order. That makes it harder to review and maintain.\n\nGenerally in Crashpad, we put x86-anything before ARM-anything.",
