      "writtenOn": "2020-03-16T20:43:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Per the way we normally log things, this would be interpreted as “the thread_state_flavor() call failed”, but that’s not right. This should name thread_get_state.\n\nWhere you have a series of thread_get_state calls as you do here, but need to disambiguate them, the string should be something like \"thread_get_state(kThreadStateFlavor)\". In ProcessReaderMac::InitializeThreads, I just let the numeric value of kThreadStateFlavor pass through to the log message.",
      "revId": "3724abf967661fa6fd6feb7a8188c2f929403985",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
